15:26.945 --> 15:29.640
Do you think this will
affect our time at Disneyland?

15:31.482 --> 15:33.731
Barry,
this is all your fault!

15:33.967 --> 15:35.648
You and your stupid
bed massager.

15:35.735 --> 15:37.836
I know! I'm not a man!

15:38.057 --> 15:41.173
I'm starting college,
but the truth is I still feel like a boy.

15:41.308 --> 15:42.708
Like sad, pathetic
little Adam here.

15:42.797 --> 15:43.797
Hey!

15:43.922 --> 15:44.974
Will you shut up?

15:45.062 --> 15:46.226
I mean, look at this!

15:46.313 --> 15:48.328
Now I'll never get to a
phone and learn the truth

15:48.415 --> 15:49.762
that I definitely
don't wanna know!

15:49.849 --> 15:50.897
My God!

15:50.984 --> 15:52.999
You're both
just selfish jerks!

15:53.086 --> 15:54.167
You know,
I actually thought

15:54.254 --> 15:56.536
I was gonna miss you next
year, but good riddance!

15:56.623 --> 15:57.703
Stop!

15:57.790 --> 15:59.039
Tell me the truth...

15:59.126 --> 16:02.414
Are you all gonna head out the door
for college and never look back?

16:04.133 --> 16:05.768
I see.

16:06.800 --> 16:09.582
Every one of these pictures
breaks my heart.

16:09.936 --> 16:12.052
You all look sad or angry
or miserable.

16:12.139 --> 16:13.859
And that is not
what I wanted.

16:14.141 --> 16:16.056
- Bevy...
- No!

16:16.143 --> 16:18.594
Let's just go home
and be done with it.

16:19.312 --> 16:21.327
I can't take another day
of family vacation

16:21.414 --> 16:23.429
if this is the last one
I'm ever gonna have.

16:27.082 --> 16:30.002
<i>Our car and
our mom were broken,</i>

16:30.090 --> 16:31.938
<i>and all we wanted
was to go home.</i>

16:32.025 --> 16:33.706
I thought we had more
suitcases than this.

16:33.793 --> 16:34.774
We did.

16:34.861 --> 16:36.392
At least this
horrible trip is over.

16:36.480 --> 16:38.744
<i>But it wasn't.
Not for my dad.</i>

16:38.831 --> 16:41.847
<i>He was about to head down
a road we never expected.</i>

16:41.934 --> 16:43.449
You know what I think?

16:43.536 --> 16:45.085
I think you're all ****
in the head.

16:45.172 --> 16:46.786
- Whoa!
- Motel language!

16:46.873 --> 16:47.887
You're just
gonna give up?

16:47.974 --> 16:48.955
- Yeah.
- Kinda.

16:49.042 --> 16:49.793
Do we have a choice?

16:49.881 --> 16:53.058
Your mom worked her ass off
to plan you a great vacation,

16:53.180 --> 16:54.699
and I didn't know why.

16:54.881 --> 16:56.996
But, damn it, I do now.

16:57.517 --> 16:58.764
Murray,
what are you saying?

16:58.851 --> 17:00.566
I'm not sure
about the future,

17:00.769 --> 17:02.802
but right here, right now,

17:02.889 --> 17:05.605
there's no amount of money
I wouldn't spend

17:05.692 --> 17:07.640
for my family
to have a great vacation.

17:07.727 --> 17:08.808
Dad's suddenly
thoughtful!

17:08.895 --> 17:10.310
He must've banged his head
in the accident!

17:10.396 --> 17:11.411
Are you serious?

17:11.498 --> 17:13.519
To keep
this family together,

17:13.863 --> 17:15.801
I would spend
every last penny.

17:17.671 --> 17:19.019
Hey, Goldbergs,
need a lift?

17:19.107 --> 17:21.150
Thank God! Everybody get in!
Come on!

17:21.238 --> 17:22.746
Geoff!
How did you find us?

17:22.834 --> 17:25.392
Well, you left my dad a lot
of very upsetting messages,

17:25.480 --> 17:26.959
so I drove here
as fast as I could.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.928
I followed your suitcases
like bread crumbs!

17:29.015 --> 17:31.027
So, what did you want
to talk to me about?

17:32.997 --> 17:34.179
Well...

17:34.321 --> 17:37.770
I had such an amazing time
doing nothing this summer,

17:37.857 --> 17:40.058
that I want it
to continue.

17:40.237 --> 17:41.637
I'm not going to school
in the fall.

17:42.380 --> 17:43.861
Oh, my God!
That's it?

17:43.949 --> 17:46.346
Well, yeah. I mean,
it's a pretty big deal.

17:46.433 --> 17:47.680
My dad's not thrilled.

17:47.767 --> 17:48.981
And your messages
didn't exactly

17:49.068 --> 17:50.650
fill him with hope
for my future.

17:50.785 --> 17:52.785
You jerk! I thought you
were breaking up with me!

17:52.910 --> 17:54.187
What? Never.

17:54.274 --> 17:56.274
You're the greatest thing
that ever happened to me.

17:56.490 --> 17:57.771
I never doubted it.

17:57.881 --> 18:00.463
<i>Turns out some trips
are about finding your way,</i>

18:00.613 --> 18:02.613
<i>and not losing track
of where you're headed.</i>

18:02.749 --> 18:04.797
Hey, Bar.
About what I said.

18:04.884 --> 18:06.466
No, you were right.

18:06.553 --> 18:07.832
I'm not ready for college.

18:07.920 --> 18:08.967
Of course you are.

18:09.058 --> 18:10.536
You're Big Tasty.

18:10.623 --> 18:13.706
You attack everything you do with
the full force of your being.

18:13.793 --> 18:16.486
Trust me, college is gonna be
a piece of cake for you.

18:16.574 --> 18:17.710
You really think so?

18:17.797 --> 18:18.931
I know so.

18:19.622 --> 18:21.113
Thanks, Ad-Rock.

18:21.535 --> 18:23.089
<i>Venturing out
can be scary,</i>

18:23.187 --> 18:24.683
<i>but it's easier
to take that trek</i>

18:24.771 --> 18:26.863
<i>when you're riding
with the people you love.</i>

18:27.035 --> 18:28.855
<i>Family vacations are hard.</i>

18:28.943 --> 18:31.793
<i>They're stressful
and expensive,</i>

18:32.074 --> 18:33.566
<i>and uncomfortable.</i>

18:33.654 --> 18:35.069
<i>But the thing
that makes them great</i>

18:35.157 --> 18:37.582
<i>are the memories
of doing it all together.</i>

18:38.011 --> 18:39.730
We're really here.

18:40.253 --> 18:41.597
Thank you, Mama.

18:42.088 --> 18:43.569
Anything for you, schmoo.

18:43.656 --> 18:45.838
Maybe next year we can go
to Walt Disney World.

18:45.925 --> 18:46.906
That sounds pretty cool.

18:46.993 --> 18:48.074
Yeah, I guess I'd try it.

18:48.161 --> 18:50.310
Wait... You guys
would wanna do this again?

18:50.397 --> 18:51.877
I'm open to it.

18:51.964 --> 18:54.605
Ah! My schmoopies
will be with me forever!

18:56.769 --> 18:58.457
Are we too late?

18:58.599 --> 19:01.144
- We got lost.
- Intentionally.

19:01.232 --> 19:03.277
Just in time, Pops!
We're running for it!

19:22.161 --> 19:24.371
Oh, sorry,
park's closed.

19:24.531 --> 19:26.779
What? Oh, no!
S-someone do something!

19:26.866 --> 19:28.364
I'm here!

19:28.535 --> 19:30.590
Don't worry, schmoo.
Mama's got this.

19:30.798 --> 19:31.779
In that moment,

19:31.867 --> 19:33.908
<i>Beverly Goldberg
did what she did best...</i>

19:33.996 --> 19:35.973
<i>She lied her ass off.</i>

19:36.061 --> 19:38.776
<i>She told elaborate,
far-fetched tales of our journey.</i>

19:38.987 --> 19:41.270
<i>Apparently,
we were attacked by bald eagles</i>

19:41.381 --> 19:43.196
<i>and a motorcycle gang?</i>

19:43.283 --> 19:46.369
<i>There was a tornado,
and then a tsunami.</i>

19:46.457 --> 19:48.278
<i>And then another tornado.</i>

19:48.366 --> 19:52.168
<i>She wove a tapestry of lies
so intricate, so beautiful,</i>

19:52.359 --> 19:54.407
<i>by the end, none of us knew
what was real.</i>

19:54.494 --> 19:55.975
..and that is when
little Adam

19:56.062 --> 19:59.044
had to help his grandpa
by sucking out the venom.

19:59.131 --> 20:02.145
Wow, you guys have been through
a whole lot as a family.

20:02.233 --> 20:04.315
And you know what? I had no idea
there were zebras in Arizona.

20:04.402 --> 20:06.184
Zebras are the piranhas
of the sand.

20:06.272 --> 20:08.853
Well, you know what?
All I meant was the park is closed now.

20:08.947 --> 20:10.645
But it opens
in 15 minutes.

20:11.648 --> 20:13.309
Why didn't you
say something?

20:13.397 --> 20:15.489
Well, I tried, but you were
going on and on and on.

20:15.582 --> 20:17.330
But go on in!
Come on, the park's all yours!

20:17.417 --> 20:18.942
Rusty, you're the best!

20:19.052 --> 20:21.291
Let's do it, Adam!
Let's go ride "Star Tours"!

20:21.379 --> 20:22.302
No, no!

20:22.389 --> 20:25.171
I think I know something that would
be more fun for the whole family.

20:25.258 --> 20:26.639
<i>♪ Holiday road</i>

20:26.825 --> 20:29.434
<i>We finally made it
to the happiest place on Earth.</i>

20:29.522 --> 20:32.076
<i>And as magical as it was,
thanks to my mom,</i>

20:32.164 --> 20:35.121
<i>I realized the best part
of the Goldberg vacation</i>

20:35.209 --> 20:36.490
<i>was the journey.</i>

20:36.689 --> 20:39.405
<i>To this day,
we still travel as a family.</i>

20:39.539 --> 20:41.204
<i>Of course,
it never gets easier,</i>

20:41.292 --> 20:43.720
<i>but I wouldn't trade it
for the world.</i>

20:45.540 --> 20:50.204
<i>- ♪ Holiday ro-o-o-o-o-o-ad ♪
- ♪ Oh whoa whoa, Oh whoa whoa! ♪</i>

20:50.384 --> 20:55.336
<i>- ♪ Holiday ro-o-o-o-o-o-o-ad ♪
- ♪ Oh whoa whoa, Oh whoa whoa! ♪</i>

21:05.147 --> 21:08.552
Wakey-wakey! Get out!
I was just dreaming about

21:08.640 --> 21:10.182
scoring a touchdown
for the Eagles!

21:10.269 --> 21:11.484
But I brought you
breakfast.

21:11.571 --> 21:12.585
Well, finally!

21:12.673 --> 21:15.029
I've been trying to take my
meals in my room for years.

21:15.117 --> 21:16.155
Gimme!

21:16.242 --> 21:17.623
This is
a whole lotta liquids.

21:17.710 --> 21:19.687
All part of
a balanced breakfast.

21:20.549 --> 21:21.863
No! My juices!

21:21.981 --> 21:23.863
Oh, no! My hot coffee!

21:23.950 --> 21:26.165
Oh, no! Adam! Hit stop!

21:26.252 --> 21:28.133
I should have never
stolen this from the motel!

21:28.220 --> 21:29.695
Yeah,
I'm gonna miss you.

